<!-- Wanted to put together cheatsheet summarizing the key HTML elements, attributes, and their purposes just for future use, both myself and others as I believe it's always good to be able to look back on things for guidance, whether you know the information by hear or not. -->

HTML Basics Cheat Sheet

1. HTML Structure
  <!DOCTYPE html>: Declares the document as HTML5.
  <html lang="en">: Root element of the page. The lang attribute specifies the language.
  <head>: Contains metadata, like the title and character encoding.
    <meta charset="utf-8">: Specifies the character encoding.
    <title>: Sets the title displayed in the browser tab.
  <body>: Contains all visible content on the page.

2. Headings
  <h1> to <h6>: Heading elements.
    <h1>: Most important heading (only one per page).
    <h2> to <h6>: Subheadings of decreasing importance.

3. Paragraph
  <p>: Creates a paragraph of text.

4. Comments
  <!-- comment text -->: Comments in HTML, not visible in the browser.

5. Main Sectioning Elements
  <main>: Wraps the main content of the webpage.
  <section>: Defines sections within a document for better organization and accessibility.

6. Links and Anchors
  <a href="url">link text</a>: Creates a hyperlink.
    href: The URL the link points to.
    target="_blank": Opens the link in a new tab.

7. Images
  <img src="image-url" alt="image description">: Adds an image to the page.
    src: URL of the image.
    alt: Description of the image for accessibility.

8. Lists
  Unordered List (Bullets):
    <ul>
      <li>Item 1</li>
      <li>Item 2</li>
      <li>Item 3</li>
    </ul>

Ordered List (Numbers):
    <ol>
      <li>Item 1</li>
      <li>Item 2</li>
      <li>Item 3</li>
    </ol>

9. Figures and Captions
<figure>: Groups images and captions together.

  <figure>
    <img src="image-url" alt="A description">
    <figcaption>Image caption</figcaption>
  </figure>

10. Emphasis and Importance
  <em>: Emphasizes text, usually italicized.
  <strong>: Indicates important text, usually bold.

11. Forms
  <form action="url">: Collects user input.

 action: URL to send the form data to.

  Text Input Field:
    <input type="text" name="input-name" placeholder="hint text" required>

   type="text": Defines a text input.
   name: The data field for the input.
   placeholder: Hint text inside the field.
   required: Ensures the field must be filled in before submission.

Button:
  <button type="submit">Submit</button>

type="submit": Submits the form.

Radio Buttons:
    <fieldset>
    <legend>Question</legend>
    <label for="option1">
      <input id="option1" type="radio" name="options" value="option1" checked> Option 1
    </label>
    <label for="option2">
      <input id="option2" type="radio" name="options" value="option2"> Option 2
    </label>
  </fieldset>

name: Groups radio buttons so only one can be selected.
checked: Pre-selects a radio button.

Checkboxes:
  <input type="checkbox" id="option1" name="group" value="option1">
  <label for="option1">Option 1</label>

12. Footer
<footer>: Defines the footer of the page.

  <footer>
    <p>No Copyright - freeCodeCamp.org</p>
  </footer>

Best Practices:
  Nesting: Always properly nest elements (e.g., headers inside sections).
  Indentation: Use two spaces to indent nested elements for readability.
  Accessibility: Use alt for images, for in labels, when needed








